>
> >So, I guess I should ask right off the bat, are there any subjects that
> >generally cause nothing but strife and disagreements on this list, e.g.
> >which oil to use, whether to do custom or stock restos, etc.?
>
> You picked two of them right off the bat.  The charter
> http://www.type2.com/vintagebuscharter.html has a little more information.
> Some other "hot topics" are tires (what size, load rating, etc), 009
> distributors pro and con, complete bonestock restos with NOS Wolfsburg
> air in the tires vs pop-rivets and Bondo, etc, etc.  Most of these topics
> don't cause flame wars so much as they are discussions that come around
> periodically - sometimes new info comes out with each iteration but
> sometimes not.
>
> You have probably found these resources already but here they are:
>
> http://www.type2.com/vintagebusreflect/  Web reflector for the
> vintagebus list.  You can't post but you can read all you like.  Handy
> to use if you're traveling or whatever and can't get to your regular
> e-mail account.
>
> http://www.type2.com/archive/search-vintagebus.html  Archive of the
> mailing list.  Lots of good info here.
>
> http://www.vintagebus.com/  Lots more good info.  This site is run
> by the moderator of the vintagebus list, Thom Fitzpatrick.
>
> The reprint of the Bentley workshop manual for '63-'67 Buses.  If you
> don't have one, get one - it answers _many_ questions.  The only thing
> it lacks is color - you can the wiring diagrams in color (scanned out of
> original manuals) at vintagebus.com .
>
> http://wow.atlasta.net/~mriluvu/oacdp/  Scanned parts manuals and
> literature, including Bus parts manuals covering '50-'54 and '58-'67.
>
> Welcome!
>
> Matt Roberds
